  <note line="41" original="ekūposathaṃ (ka.)" reference-line="17" id="4">
    <extra></extra>
    <alternatives>
      <alternative source-abbr="vri" source="vipassana research institut">ekuposathaṃ</alternative>
      <alternative source-abbr="ka." source="cambodian">ekūposathaṃ</alternative>
    </alternatives>
    <type>auto</type>
    <snippet>. Yāvatā samantā nimittā kittitā. Yadi saṅghassa pattakallaṃ, saṅgho etehi nimittehi sīmaṃ sammanneyya samānasaṃvāsaṃ ekuposathaṃ </snippet>
  </note>
  <note line="50" original="sammati (syā.)" reference-line="18" id="5">
    <extra></extra>
    <alternatives>
      <alternative source-abbr="vri" source="vipassana research institut">sammuti</alternative>
      <alternative source-abbr="syā." source="thai">sammati</alternative>
    </alternatives>
    <type>auto</type>
    <snippet>Suṇātu me, bhante, saṅgho. Yāvatā samantā nimittā kittitā. Saṅgho etehi nimittehi sīmaṃ sammannati samānasaṃvāsaṃ ekuposathaṃ. Yassāyasmato khamati etehi nimittehi sīmāya sammuti </snippet>
  </note>
  <note line="59" original="nadīpāraṃ sīmaṃ (sī. syā.)" reference-line="20" id="6">
    <extra></extra>
    <alternatives>
      <alternative source-abbr="vri" source="vipassana research institut">nadīpārasīmaṃ</alternative>
      <alternative source-abbr="sī." source="sri lanka">nadīpāraṃ sīmaṃ</alternative>
      <alternative source-abbr="syā." source="thai">nadīpāraṃ sīmaṃ</alternative>
    </alternatives>
    <type>auto</type>
    <snippet>Tena kho pana samayena chabbaggiyā bhikkhū nadīpārasīmaṃ </snippet>
  </note>
  <note line="69" original="samuhanitvā (ka.)" reference-line="25" id="7">
    <extra></extra>
    <alternatives>
      <alternative source-abbr="vri" source="vipassana research institut">samūhanitvā</alternative>
      <alternative source-abbr="ka." source="cambodian">samuhanitvā</alternative>
    </alternatives>
    <type>auto</type>
    <snippet>. Na, bhikkhave, ekasmiṃ āvāse dve uposathāgārāni sammannitabbāni. Yo sammanneyya, āpatti dukkaṭassa. Anujānāmi, bhikkhave, ekaṃ samūhanitvā </snippet>
  </note>
  <note line="78" original="samuhaneyya (ka.)" reference-line="26" id="8">
    <extra></extra>
    <alternatives>
      <alternative source-abbr="vri" source="vipassana research institut">samūhaneyya</alternative>
      <alternative source-abbr="ka." source="cambodian">samuhaneyya</alternative>
    </alternatives>
    <type>auto</type>
    <snippet>Suṇātu me, bhante, saṅgho. Yadi saṅghassa pattakallaṃ, saṅgho itthannāmaṃ uposathāgāraṃ samūhaneyya </snippet>
  </note>
  <note line="87" original="uposathamukhaṃ (syā.)" reference-line="29" id="9">
    <extra></extra>
    <alternatives>
      <alternative source-abbr="vri" source="vipassana research institut">uposathappamukhaṃ</alternative>
      <alternative source-abbr="syā." source="thai">uposathamukhaṃ</alternative>
    </alternatives>
    <type>auto</type>
    <snippet> nu kho’’ti. Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ. Sammatāya vā, bhikkhave, bhūmiyā nisinnā asammatāya vā yato pātimokkhaṃ suṇāti, katovassa uposatho. Tena hi, bhikkhave, saṅgho yāva mahantaṃ uposathappamukhaṃ </snippet>
  </note>
  <note line="96" original="tena cīvarānissa (ka.)" reference-line="35" id="10">
    <extra></extra>
    <alternatives>
      <alternative source-abbr="vri" source="vipassana research institut">cīvarānissa</alternative>
      <alternative source-abbr="ka." source="cambodian">tena cīvarānissa</alternative>
    </alternatives>
    <type>auto</type>
    <snippet> kho pana samayena āyasmā mahākassapo andhakavindā rājagahaṃ uposathaṃ āgacchanto antarāmagge nadiṃ taranto manaṃ vūḷho ahosi, cīvarānissa </snippet>
  </note>
  <note line="105" original="avippavāsassa (syā.)" reference-line="37" id="11">
    <extra></extra>
    <alternatives>
      <alternative source-abbr="vri" source="vipassana research institut">avippavāsāya</alternative>
      <alternative source-abbr="syā." source="thai">avippavāsassa</alternative>
    </alternatives>
    <type>auto</type>
    <snippet>Suṇātu me, bhante, saṅgho. Yā sā saṅghena sīmā sammatā samānasaṃvāsā ekuposathā, saṅgho taṃ sīmaṃ ticīvarena avippavāsaṃ sammannati. Yassāyasmato khamati etissā sīmāya ticīvarena avippavāsāya </snippet>
  </note>
  <note line="114" original="avippavāso (syā.)" reference-line="37" id="12">
    <extra></extra>
    <alternatives>
      <alternative source-abbr="vri" source="vipassana research institut">avippavāsā</alternative>
      <alternative source-abbr="syā." source="thai">avippavāso</alternative>
    </alternatives>
    <type>auto</type>
    <snippet> sammuti, so tuṇhassa; yassa nakkhamati, so bhāseyya. Sammatā sā sīmā saṅghena ticīvarena avippavāsā </snippet>
  </note>
  <note line="123" original="avippavāsassa (syā.)" reference-line="40" id="13">
    <extra></extra>
    <alternatives>
      <alternative source-abbr="vri" source="vipassana research institut">avippavāsāya</alternative>
      <alternative source-abbr="syā." source="thai">avippavāsassa</alternative>
    </alternatives>
    <type>auto</type>
    <snippet>Suṇātu me, bhante, saṅgho. Yā sā saṅghena sīmā sammatā samānasaṃvāsā ekuposathā, saṅgho taṃ sīmaṃ ticīvarena avippavāsaṃ sammannati, ṭhapetvā gāmañca gāmūpacārañca. Yassāyasmato khamati etissā sīmāya ticīvarena avippavāsāya </snippet>
